snippet.textDisplay:
Some folks on social media claim that drinking bleach will cure Coronavirus. During the early days of AIDS there were dozens of crazy "cures" suggested, including bleach, mushrooms, blood-heating....Sadly, there is STILL no cure for HIV/AIDS. Viruses are NOT bacteria. They are totally different life forms. Antibiotics like penicillin, a toxin produced by bread mold, kill bacteria regardless of the type of infecting bacteria. But antibiotics or "general" anti-viral drugs fail to kill viruses. Antibodies and vaccines must target the specific strains of infecting virus or they will not work well, though there is often some cross-reactivity. That is why the flu vaccine must be changed each year, to match the dominant circulating strains of influenza. Remember "The Stand" by Stephen King? I do NOT think this "new" Coronavirus will be as bad as "Captain Tripps,"-the death rate is about 2%, much lower than Ebola, which has an estimated mortality rate of 20-40%. There are reports of Coronavirus cases in Massachusetts, Phoenix, Orange County, CA, Chicago, Texas and Minnesota as well as in Washington State. "Conspiracy theory" rumors abound. For example: "Dr. Francis Boyle, creator of U.S. Bio-weapons Act, claims Coronavirus is a Biological Weapon"---"DC Clothesline." "A U.S. Patent for an "Attenuated Coronavirus was filed in 2015 and granted in 2018," according to the "DC Clothesline." Rumors are now circulating on Social Media about a "high level exercise" three months ago by a health organization funded by Bill Gates to estimate fatalities from a Coronavirus "Pandemic" in the U.S.A. Speculation that eating "bat soup" or bat flesh is the origin of the Wuhan Coronavirus has seemingly been proven correct through DNA analysis- bat Coronavirus DNA matches that of Coronavirus in the Wuhan outbreak. Since I never visited Wuhan while I lived in China from 2014-2016, and haven't eaten bats, I have NO personal knowledge about the veracity of these rumors. (Btw, how HAS Ozzie Osbourne been doing lately, since he allegedly bit off that poor bat's head during a Black Sabbath concert?) Bats are known carriers and vectors of many diseases, including rabies, which infects the brain, and bats also carry the deadly Ebola virus. I arrived in China the year after the SARS outbreak, which began at meat markets in Guangzhou. I taught college in Beijing from 2004-2009. China is efficient, fast and practical in dealing with disease outbreaks. They do not hesitate to quarantine people: my college students told me they had to stay in their dorms during the SARS outbreak. The following story appeared in "Global Research News": Dr. Michael Ryan, Executive Director of the WHO Health Emergencies Program, stated that
“China and Chinese scientists have performed probably the most rapid characterization of a novel pathogen in history, and that was shared immediately. Multiple sequences were shared immediately on global platforms.”
Previously Dr. Ryan had commented on his visit to China in the previous days, stating that
“China is doing the right things, and China is responding in a massive way….What I took away from that mission was the absolute, relentless and focused determination of the government of China to put the health of people in China ahead of anything else at this point, and to take what are significant economic and other hits in order to put the health of people first...
“I was involved in 2002/2003 in SARS, and I can tell you from direct operational experience that there is no comparison between the behaviour of China then and the behaviour of China now.”
He described the responses of all countries which had been affected thus far, including China, as “remarkably transparent.”---"Global Research News" ALL viral outbreaks must be taken seriously. Fortunately, the death rate per # of infections from this "new" Wuhan Coronavirus seems fairly low so far, about 2%, similar to the death rate from SARS. This Coronavirus is related to the SARS Coronavirus and is, like SARS, a "zoonotic" disease of non-human origin. It is not nearly as deadly as Ebola, which has an estimated mortality rate up to 40% and is not as easily transmitted as influenza, the Norovirus intestinal bug or the common cold. Viruses are often limited to one species, but many types of viruses jump from one species to another. Rabies, Zika, Ebola, EIA, SARS, MERS, Hantavirus, and HIV are a few examples. The current worldwide HIV/AIDS epidemic began when humans were infected by HIV-infected chimpanzees in tropical Africa, which probably happened on numerous occasions over past centuries or millennia. Zika was first discovered in Uganda in 1947 and can also infect monkeys, chimpanzees, bats and pigs. It is believed that one or two soccer fans attending World Cup Games brought Zika to Brazil. There was an outbreak of Ebola virus several years ago with 11,000 deaths in three small West African nations. There is currently a very serious Ebola outbreak in the Congo. Rabies, which is almost 100% fatal unless vaccine treatment is begun quickly, can infect almost all species of mammals except opossums. Rabies is commonly spread by bats, skunks, and raccoons in the wild, and by domestic cats and dogs.The various types of HIV viruses have existed far longer than previously thought. "African Slim Disease" was studied by a top Harvard research team headed by Matthew Alan Gonda and Dr. Myron "Max" Essex. Their study was published in the Journal "Nature" and estimated that the average time from date of infection to death is about 12 years. "African Slim Disease" is caused by HIV-1, the main circulating type of Human Immune Virus. HIV was likely first spread to humans by bonobos or chimpanzees, probably on a number of occasions. Modern 20th-Century transportation allowed HIV-1 to spread quickly from small, isolated villages in Sub-Saharan Africa to cities throughout Africa. Regional and international travel then allowed HIV to spread worldwide during the 20th Century. Haiti has long had a very high incidence of HIV. There were rumors of a "new, fatal" STD long prior to the official joint announcement by Dr. Robert Gallo of the USA and Dr. Luc Montagnier of the Pasteur Institute in France of the "discovery" of the Human Immune Virus as the cause of GRID ("Gay-Related Immune Deficiency," later called AIDS "Acquired Immune Deficiency Syndrome"). The first proven death from HIV was that of a teenage boy in St. Louis, Missouri, who passed away in 1969 from mysterious symptoms. His tissue samples were frozen and later tested positive for HIV. There is still NO CURE for Ebola, HIV or any other viral disease. In 1993 I suggested using strain-specific monoclonal antibodies in my HIV/STD Control Branch (Division of Epidemiology, NC State Department of Health) quarterly narrative to the CDC as a treatment for HIV, in conjunction with "therapeutic" vaccines to improve our natural immune response against HIV-infected cells. Infusion of antibodies is called "passive immunotherapy" and has been used in pediatric AIDS cases, but not for adults infected with HIV. Recent studies show that monoclonal antibodies can successfully help treat Ebola, and that "therapeutic" vaccinations help fight Simian Immune Virus (SIV) in monkeys. There are excellent results in viral suppression and increases of CD4 cells from a new antibody-based experimental drug, as reported in a leading AIDS magazine. The obvious way to treat any virus is to augment and supplement the body's natural immune response against the specific strains of the infecting virus. I suggest screening all international travelers for contagious diseases, and quarantining those who test positive. snippet.textOriginal:
Some folks on social media claim that drinking bleach will cure Coronavirus. During the early days of AIDS there were dozens of crazy "cures" suggested, including bleach, mushrooms, blood-heating....Sadly, there is STILL no cure for HIV/AIDS. Viruses are NOT bacteria. They are totally different life forms. Antibiotics like penicillin, a toxin produced by bread mold, kill bacteria regardless of the type of infecting bacteria. But antibiotics or "general" anti-viral drugs fail to kill viruses. Antibodies and vaccines must target the specific strains of infecting virus or they will not work well, though there is often some cross-reactivity. That is why the flu vaccine must be changed each year, to match the dominant circulating strains of influenza. Remember "The Stand" by Stephen King? I do NOT think this "new" Coronavirus will be as bad as "Captain Tripps,"--the death rate is about 2%, much lower than Ebola, which has an estimated mortality rate of 20-40%. There are reports of Coronavirus cases in Massachusetts, Phoenix, Orange County, CA, Chicago, Texas and Minnesota as well as in Washington State. "Conspiracy theory" rumors abound. For example: "Dr. Francis Boyle, creator of U.S. Bio-weapons Act, claims Coronavirus is a Biological Weapon"---"DC Clothesline." "A U.S. Patent for an "Attenuated Coronavirus was filed in 2015 and granted in 2018," according to the "DC Clothesline." Rumors are now circulating on Social Media about a "high level exercise" three months ago by a health organization funded by Bill Gates to estimate fatalities from a Coronavirus "Pandemic" in the U.S.A. Speculation that eating "bat soup" or bat flesh is the origin of the Wuhan Coronavirus has seemingly been proven correct through DNA analysis-- bat Coronavirus DNA matches that of Coronavirus in the Wuhan outbreak. Since I never visited Wuhan while I lived in China from 2014-2016, and haven't eaten bats, I have NO personal knowledge about the veracity of these rumors. (Btw, how HAS Ozzie Osbourne been doing lately, since he allegedly bit off that poor bat's head during a Black Sabbath concert?) “I was involved in 2002/2003 in SARS, and I can tell you from direct operational experience that there is no comparison between the behaviour of China then and the behaviour of China now.”

There was an outbreak of Ebola virus several years ago with 11,000 deaths in three small West African nations. There is currently a very serious Ebola outbreak in the Congo. Rabies, which is almost 100% fatal unless vaccine treatment is begun quickly, can infect almost all species of mammals except opossums. Rabies is commonly spread by bats, skunks, and raccoons in the wild, and by domestic cats and dogs.The various types of HIV viruses have existed far longer than previously thought. Their study was published in the Journal "Nature" and estimated that the average time from date of infection to death is about 12 years.
